  "texts": [
    "Using a VLM, we produce three complementary instructions: (i) a short imperative, (ii) a multi-step decomposition, and (iii) a natural, human-like request.",
    "When the dataset already provides a human-written instruction, we keep it and augment it with these three variants.",
    "Otherwise, we sample representative frames from the start, middle, and end of the chunk and prompt the VLM to propose task instructions.",
    "3D Point Tracking with Camera Pose and Depth PredictionWe extract 3D traces from videos with camera motion by recovering per-frame traces from each camera viewpoint.",
    "Flow-based modelDino SigLIP … Unproject to 3D using the sensor depth map Given language, RGB, and depth inputs, text is encoded by a frozen T5 encoder, RGB images are processed by DINOv3 and SigLIP, and depth maps are passed through a SigLIP encoder with a learnable stem adapter."
